{
	"$schema": "https://aka.ms/codetour-schema",
	"title": "Navigation System & Dropdowns",
	"steps": [
		{
			"file": "src/data/navData.json",
			"description": "`navData.json` controls your site's navigation. Each entry has a **key** (display text), **url** (path), and optional **children** array for dropdown menus. The `<DynamicHeader />` component automatically generates the navigation from this data. Add, remove, or modify entries here to change your site's navigation structure, **or** delete this file and manage your navigation directly in the `<StaticHeader />` Header component.",
			"line": 2
		},
		{
			"file": "src/components/Header/DynamicHeader.astro",
			"description": "The `<DynamicHeader />` component imports navData.json and loops through each nav item. It checks if an item has children - if yes, it renders as a dropdown (li.cs-li.cs-dropdown). If no children, it renders as a regular link. The current page gets the **.cs-active** class automatically based on URL matching.",
			"line": 45
		},
		{
			"file": "src/components/Settings/Settings.astro",
			"description": "`Settings.astro` is the header's utility bar — it renders the language switcher and dark mode toggle side by side. This is the file to edit when you want to swap or remove either component.\n\n**To swap the dark mode toggle**, replace the import and JSX tag. Two options live in `src/components/DarkMode/`:\n- `DarkModeToggle` — simple moon/sun button\n- `ThemeSelect` — three-way Light / Dark / Auto dropdown\n\n**To swap the language switcher**, replace the import and JSX tag. Two options live in `src/components/LanguageSwitch/`:\n- `TwoLocalesSelect` — EN/FR button toggle\n- `MultiLocalesSelect` — compact dropdown for 3+ locales\n\nThis component appears twice in `DynamicHeader` — once inside the mobile slide-out panel (`cs-shown`) and once in the desktop nav bar (`cs-hidden`). Edits here apply to both breakpoints automatically.",
			"line": 1
		},
		{
			"file": "src/assets/js/nav.js",
			"description": "`nav.js` holds the script that adds interactivity to the navigation: **Mobile menu toggle** (hamburger button), **Dropdown accessibility** (keyboard navigation with Enter/Escape), and **Focus management**. It's wrapped in the `'astro:page-load'` event to work with Astro's View Transitions — this ensures the script re-runs after each client-side navigation. Paste your CodeStitch JS here.",
			"line": 1
		}
	]
}
